<UserId.>116868473614276623003<//UserId.><user_name>John Woo</user_name>< review>
I was expecting a bit too much. I read the reviews before entering and I was a bit let down.

The place is clean and the staff are friendly. As for the food.  The menu needs a little work as it is a bit hard to navigate. At least for someone who is new and doesn't automatically know what they want.

The service bar area where they keep the napkins and such could use a few more spices or sauces. They practically had nothing and adding sauces and things to the broth is like half the fun of having Asian noodles.

Also, the store's definition of tonkatsu is different from what I expected.

Other than that the food was good, the broth was nice and rich.

However I thought it was a bit pricy for what you get and also the very disappointing plastic bowl it came in.</review>

< username>
kimberlie eddy< /username>
<time>1531629021321<//time><rate>5</rate><text>Very kind ppl and yummy pho</text><Pics>None< /Pics>< Response>

< gmap_id>
0x80c2bf37dfc3ef1d:0xe4d4310a9e59b7e4<//gmap_id>
</record></dataset><record>
<userid>107432612639662617077<//userid><user_name>Anthony Minier (DJ AnthonyM)</user_name><GmapID>0x80c2bf37dfc3ef1d:0xe4d4310a9e59b7e4<//GmapID>< Review>
This is a Noodle World Jr. not a Noodle World. What is the difference? They are the same restaurant but Noodle World Jr. has a much smaller (pared down if you will) menu. If you have ever been to Noodle World in Westwood you know that they offer a very large selection of Asian noodle based dishes from many different Asian countries. Noodle World Jr. offers the most popular dishes from different Asian countries. So basically, the dishes that both Noodle World and Noodle World Jr. offer are the same recipe but Noodle World has a much larger selection of different dishes to choose from. If you find that you can be somewhat indecisive when presented with a large selection of choices, Noodle World Jr. just might be the better option for you. The very best of the best is on the menu at Noodle World Jr. and since I have never had an Asian noodle dish that I did not like at the Noodle World in Westwood, you sort of can't lose when choosing from the best of the best. While this Noodle World Jr. seems to be more popular for lunch than for dinner (I highly suspect that that is because of the many people that are employed by the Gower Sunset studios), this is still a great option for dinner as well. This is well made and healthy Asian food at decent prices. You just can't go wrong here.</Review>

<Text>Restoring an older Acura and not only did Extreme Auto Parts have the exact glove box I was looking for, they took the time to work with me and verify some detailed aspects of it with additional photos.  Also as the glove box is susceptible to damage in transit, I asked them to overpack and then shrink wrap the glove box as I am on the other side of the country from Extreme Auto and née it was going to be a rough journey through the Fedex ground carrier.  When the glove box arrived today, the packaging was nothing short of a piece of art as the guys in the shipping department literally shaped the box in or origami like folds around the overpacking of the glove box that was then shrink wrapped and the packed in this beautiful form of a box that was obviously packed by a professional in the shipping department who really takes their job seriously and artfully.   I know I’m gushing about the way it was packaged, however I rarely get salvaged parts in such exquisite condition or shipped with such care. I’m sure your like me and are really upset when you order a product only to find it was destroyed in transit because someone in the shipping department simply did not have the right resources to do their job right or simply just did not care.  This was not the case and the  glove box arrived in pristine condition just like the photos supplied by Extreme prior to my purchase.  This was my first purchase with these guys and the whole experience simply reminds me of how everyone used to care about their job and take pride in their service and product.   Well if this first purchasing experience was any indication, I have found a great company to work with in connection with my auto restoration part needs.   Old world service, pride and care in the modern world today pretty much sums up my first experience with Extreme.<//Text><user_id>117165343145465256067<//user_id>< time>

I ordered a door lock actuator for my 2010 Toyota Prius. It's only a slight exaggeration to say they put the part in the mail the second they received my order. I received it two days sooner than expected and it was exactly as advertised and worked as expected.

< Review>
I have been here twice now (can't believe I haven't been at iLanet after all these years). There are 2 sections as of this writing: smoking sittings area near at the main place and non-smoking to the right side. The food is decent but you come here more for the atmosphere. This place is more packed during the breakfast brunch hours especially on the weekends. The selection is quite good from various sunny side eggs plates and plenty of basic Vietnamese dishes. If you haven't tried, order the Vietnamese iced coffee with condensed milk! The waiters are hustling their best but the service has been fine for me, be patient and be prepared to wait when you come here during peak hours.< /Review>

<UserId.>113572349603455848322< /UserId.><user_name>Bekah S</user_name>< text>
This is my favorite place to get sushi in Lake Forest. I ordered the sashimi plate (I think 10 piece?) plus two of the tuna belly. It was all very fresh, and nicely presented. It may be one of the best sashimi plates I have gotten in the USA. Service is a tiny bit slow but the entire place has a relaxed atmosphere. My husband got Udon with chicken, it was so big he couldn't finish it, but I think it would make a great item to share between two or more people. This is definitely a surprise for the area which can be hard to find good food in.
It is kind of tucked away in a shopping center, the parking lot is not on a main street but it is easy enough to find and I feel that parking is usually not a problem.
I would go here again. Probably wouldn't bring my kids but I think there are enough options that they would enjoy if I decided to take them here.</text>

<review>They are amazing! Food is amazing - tasty and fresh, service is amazing - everyone is quick and polite. Love the sushi bar with hot green tea, the kitchen is delicious too. < review>
(Translated by Google) The taste is perfect as a Japanese food. An abundant menu including sushi, udon, yakisoba, and bowls. However, there is a little more for Japanese to eat. Tempura Udon is not the best udon and tempura, but if tempura is on it (with the appropriate tempura). Izakaya Tenko in the neighborhood is an affiliated store and seems to have the same menu.

(Original)
日本食として味は申し分ない。すし、うどん、やきそば、どんぶりものなど、豊富なメニュー。ただ日本人が食べるにはやや量が多い。天ぷらうどんが、うどんと天ぷらでなく、天ぷらが乗った(それにふさわしい天ぷらで)あれば最高だが。近所にあるIzakaya Tenkoは系列店で、同じメニューのようだ。< /review>

< Text>
Everything about my experience was EXCEPTIONAL. I have spent the last four years working in the Optometry field in Texas and more than 25 years wearing vision correction and I can honestly (and pretty knowledgeably) say that Torrey Highlands Optometry offered the best overall experience I’ve ever had at an eye appointment!!!  Dr. Rameril was so thorough and knowledgeable in the exam room, but also very friendly and HILARIOUS! I felt he took his time to get an accurate prescription with state-of-the-art technology. Then he passed me on to the optician who worked one-on-one with me to help me find the perfect glasses and went over my benefits with me quickly and efficiently. She was so kind when I took my sweet time making decisions. Their glasses selection IS smaller than some others I’ve seen, but they clearly put a LOT of thought into the frame lines they carry and the women’s frames are so cute!!!  The whole practice seems to have adapted so well to the new, necessary protocols that arose with COVID-19 and I felt everything was clean and sanitized.  Knowing what I know about the ins-and-outs of Optometry, I whole heartedly recommend Torrey Highlands.< /Text>

He quickly wrote an upgraded prescription for glasses and copied the same to contact lenses prescription. Even though we paid for contact lens fitting, but contact lens fitting was done, only the copy-paste of glasses prescription to another page.

Generally, Contact lens prescriptions and eyeglass prescriptions are not the same. They are significantly different because eyeglass lenses are positioned approximately 12 millimeters from your eyes, whereas contact lenses rest directly on the surface of your eyes. Having a wrong prescription may lead to serious damage to vision and regular uncomfortable. The Dr. prescribed without even asking and telling, discussing what prescription was written. Previously we always were given 10 to 20% fewer prescription numbers for contact and worked very well.

<rate>5</rate><text>The front staff is courteous, personable, and experienced. My husband was new to glasses and she led him through the process of good frames to look for for his lens type and then again on what to expect when wearing progressives. I’m an old timer in contacts. She assisted me with how to obtain a rebate for my annual order and what to include with the form. Super nice to have her assistance!

Now for the biggest part...the eye exam. The office is clean, stylish, and has newer technology. Prior to being seen, they provide the standard eye tests for pressure etc,  along with a special glimpse of your eye that can actually see into the back of your eye!  For an extra $10, you can have that full eye pic taken so the Dr. and you can view to learn even more about your eye health.

The Drs. are young professionals, friendly, knowledgeable, and again, personable. They explain what changes, if any, that your eyes have had, or that your eyes have been stable for a period of years and that you might be a candidate for LASIK. Although they don’t provide LASIK there, they have successfully referred many patients to particular local LASIK surgery centers.

I have seen a multitude of eye Drs. for 28 years and I truly appreciate their service from start to finish. Even the new patient registration and scheduling center is easy as both are online. They provide annual reminders for your eye exams and I’ve found appointments available during my desired time within a week. Their location is easy to find and there is plenty of parking.

Thank you Torrey Highlands for always providing our family with exceptional service!</text><Pictures>None< /Pictures>< Response>

< Review>
I am a property owner who has used Noble for over 5 years and I give them FIVE STARS for the following reasons:
1) They vet their tenants (at least, mine) thoroughly. I have never had an issue with bad tenants.
2) When the current tenants give their notice to vacate, Noble proactively finds suitable tenants immediately. The only lapse in tenant occupancy is the time necessary to have cleaners thoroughly clean the place, which is about a week.
3) The occasional out-of-the-ordinary issue (e.g. plumbing issue, necessary tree trimming, etc) is handled seamlessly, and the contracted services are always at affordable and competitive rates. Charges are reflected on the monthly statement which facilitates filing taxes at tax time.
4) I had a very recent issue where an incoming tenant requested new carpeting. Since I hadn't been down to San Diego in a couple years (I intend to eventually move back in to that house, I'm currently renting up in Northern California), I hadn't seen the condition of the carpeting. I deferred to Noble, and they said the place needed new carpeting. So - even though this expenditure comes at a bad time - I gave the green light. That said, Noble does a commendable job in maintaining the material condition of the property, which is to the benefit of both the tenant and the property owner.

In order for this system to work optimally, a sense of responsibility and effective communication must exist and be a two way street between both property management company and tenant, as well as property owner and property management company. That has been my positive experience with Noble Real Estate Services.< /Review>

There are limits on the amount of the security deposit:

If the security deposit is for a residential property without furniture, the security deposit may equal 2 times the rent.
If the residence is furnished, the landlord may charge up to 3 times the rent.
There is no restriction on the amount of the security deposit for the rental of a commercial property.<//Text><Pictures>None</Pictures><Response>None< /Response>< GmapID>

< user>
108898452716081782959< /user>
<Gmap_id>0x80c2cc66e1bc12af:0xb8a3deec1fe04b82< /Gmap_id>< Review>
After placing an order on this same model of bike in the color "Summer", a week later I was notified that suddenly the bike was out of stock. It wasn’t out of stock when I ordered it but suddenly it was now. I was disappointed, but they told me they had the bike available in "Misty Blue" and I told them to go ahead and send that one to me. Upon receiving the bike, which was in a LARGE box sitting on my porch after the FedEx guy just dropped it there without notifying me, I opened it up to put it together. There were no assembly instructions to be found. Before you say that I should have taken it to a professional bike mechanic, understand that there is a pandemic and I was pretty confident that I could put it together myself (and it came with tools to assemble it, which implies that you can do it yourself). However, no assembly instructions made this VERY difficult. So I emailed Mr.Bikes and asked if I could have some assembly instructions so I could put my bike together. No response after two days, when they had no problem responding right away when I told them to go ahead and send the bike in a different color. So at that point, I decided to go off of the photo of the bike and common sense and put it together within 3 hours. I must also add that the screw to adjust the seat was too short and had been stripped, so I had to go out and buy a new, longer screw to even be able to ride the bike at my adjusted height. It’s been a week since emailing them for assembly instructions and still no response. But I certainly got an email asking me to review my purchase. I wasn’t planning on it, but since that was so much more important than sending me instructions to assemble the bike that wasn’t even the color I ordered in the first place, here I am, leaving a review. Thanks for the bike Mr. Bikes but also thanks for the most minimal help imaginable. Proceed with caution, to those who are interested in purchasing a bike. These people do this a lot, and worse. Look them up on the Better Business Bureau, you won’t like what you see.<//Review>

< text>
I ordered two BMX bikes for my kids and they absolutely love their bikes. I placed my order on 4/15 then got worried that I may not receive my order after reading some of the reviews. I immediately emailed them the next morning to make sure that what I ordered was actually in stock. It took a while to get a response but after sending a few messages and calling, I got a response that one of the bikes wasn't in stock after all. I was able to switch my order order something that was actually in stock and received the bikes on 4/27 to Oregon. As long as you verify that the product you want is in stock, I highly recommend ordering from Mr Bike Shop.<//text>

The design of bikes were outstanding for very reasonable prices. Not only that, they are offering “order today, shipping today” or something like that. I was very excited waiting for my bike, I download the app to track my shipment. Everything sounds fantastic.

After a few days (4) I realized the status of my order didn’t change. I call and they said it will be shipped that day... nothing happened. I sent a couple of emails through the weekends with no response. I called on Monday (8 days after my order) and they said they would call me back but they didn’t so I called again.

They promised again it would be sent that day... NOTHING! I called again today (9 days after the order) to find out that the tires that they were waiting for are there but now the frame is missing.

My order got canceled and my refund is pending. Whoever that was dealing with my case couldn’t be bothered to give me any other options so at least I could have had a bike sent to me. I never asked for a discount either a refund. I wanted a bike delivered, in exchange of the money I paid...

Ordered a bike online from these guys and instantly got a confirmation order but nothing else after that. After not receiving anything after a week I was told by a representative over the phone that my bike was to be shipped out later that day. However it was not. A few days later I pulled up and questioned them as to where my bike was. The guy I believe his name was tony, called someone at their warehouse and said they couldn't seem to find it and they didn't have the white one (Aventon Mataro). But they still sold me the bike. They are known to sell inventory that they don't even have. They take your money and will hold onto it until you go and do something about it. In the store they were able to get me a different and actually more expensive bike at an even exchange. Good customer service in store, but online is sketch. DO NOT ORDER ONLINE. Only reason I got what I paid for is because I am local and was able to pull up on them.< /text>

<Review>Scummers for online orders. Cant attest to their brick n mortor shop but DO NOT order online. Never answer the phone, no return of emails or messages left  but they charge your card. Order 8723. Scammers. You dont take peoples orders who are buying Christmas gifts for their kids and not respond to their email or repeated phone calls for over 2 days.  Wish I had read prior to order placement.

SAVE YOURSELF THE HASSLE.

11/30/18 UPDATE:  I involved the bike manufacturer which actually got me a call back.   I was  cursed at over this google review.  Ramon admitted they did not have the bike on hand even though it was on "sale" on their website.  However, I was charged immediately for my purchase.  He refunded my $$ minus a "25% restock fee".   Apparently, they dont know you have to actually SHIP something and have the customer  RETURN it to RE-STOCK it.  So this is the crux of their scam.  They take your $$, ship nothing, then charge a 25% restock fee.  I will get my $$ back from Visa when I dispute this claim,  but this is fraudulent and shows their unscrupulous online "business" practice.

I wish I had read the 77 and counting 1 star reviews that expose their scam ahead and saved myself all this hassle.< /Review><pics>None</pics>< Response>

<Text>DO NOT BUY FROM THEIR ONLINE STORE. There are mixed reviews on here about their online store - I thought I'd give them the benefit of the doubt and give them a go, but that didn't turn out in my favor at all. Spent $500 USD on a bike but thankfully PayPal has my back and I got a refund after I disputed it after waiting 30 days for seemingly nothing; despite when I did get a call from them (coincidentally nearly immediately I filed the PayPal dispute) they said they 'shipped it' 10 days prior to the dispute and gave me a dummy tracking number which showed that the thing hadn't even been picked up by FedEx. The one thing I didn't get back however was the time I wasted trying to even get a response from this 'business'. They seem to have a legit brick and mortar store but their online store is an absolute scam - worst customer service I've ever dealt with hands down. They are that bad they even let the PayPal dispute timeout (i.e. they didn't respond to the dispute in under 10 days) which then means that PayPal automatically refunds the money to me - if that's any indication of how they run their business. If you value your time, don't even bother looking on their website or even going into their physical store for that matter if they treat their physical business the same as their online business. < review>
(Translated by Google) I have already made several orders to the web with shipping to Spain and in all, without exception, the communication has been terrible.
Last time I ordered a complete bike and as usual they shipped it in two separate packages. Well, after weeks without receiving news of the second package, I was forced to contact the store, in search of some type of shipping information related to it. Nothing. When they are not interested, they do not take calls, or SMS, or emails, or messages on social networks. They even blocked me.
Finally, and after using all my energy to get in touch with them, they deigned to send the remaining package, which I received, of course, much later than expected at the time of ordering.
In addition, at the time of receiving both packages, I had to take care of the customs amounts (an additional € 37 per package).
It is up to each one to assess whether it is worth risking money in this way to save a few euros.
Good product, lousy service.

(Original)
He hecho ya varios pedidos a la web con envío a España y en todos, sin excepción, la comunicación ha sido pésima.
La última vez pedí una bici completa y, como de costumbre, la enviaron en dos paquetes por separado. Pues bien, tras semanas sin recibir noticia del segundo paquete, me vi obligado a contactar con la tienda, en busca de algún tipo de información de envío relativa al mismo. Nada. Cuando no les interesa, no atienden ni llamadas, ni SMS, ni correos, ni mensajes por redes sociales. Llegaron incluso a bloquearme.
Finalmente y tras emplear toda mi energía en conseguir comunicarme con ellos, se dignaron a enviar el paquete restante, el cual recibí, por supuesto, muchísimo más tarde de lo esperado en el momento de realizar el pedido.
Además, a la hora de recibir ambos paquetes, tuve que hacerme cargo de los importes de aduana (unos 37€ adicionales por paquete).
En mano de cada uno queda valorar si merece la pena arriesgar el dinero de esta manera por ahorrar unos cuántos euros.
Buen producto, pésimo servicio.</review>
